name: #Slack
description: Slack is a cloud-based set of proprietary team collaboration tools and services.

licenses.description: See license plans at Slack.com - not allowed for commercial use.

usecases.name: Development team instant messaging
usecases.description: Developer commuication channel, for instant messaging, designed to improve a teams fusion with its Continuos Delivery pipeline.

usecases.name: Storage of machine secrets
usecases.description: Although slack makes secrets like data passwords easily accessible, it is a terrible idea to use it for sensitive information. Even worse, than a yellow postit note with the db password on your desk.

usecases.name: Hook up of Software Life Cycle Development tools
usecases.description: Many teams like to have messages from the continuos delivery pipleine streamed in as part of the team conversation. Also alerts and monitoring events could make their way into the teams slack channel.

debt.description: Design of connectivity adapter seems broken, and has been reported as an error in backlog for a the last 6 months without a fix.
Setup with copying data trough zones seems redundant.

comments.description: I experience problems when reconnecting, will report this as tech debt

name: .Net
description: .NET Framework is a software framework developed by Microsoft that runs primarily on Microsoft Windows. It includes a large class library named Framework Class Library (FCL) and provides language interoperability (each language can use code written in other languages) across several programming languages.
usecases: May be used for development targeted the Windows platform.

name: 7-zip
description: 7-Zip is a free and open-source file archiver, a utility used to place groups of files within compressed containers known as archives.
usecases: 7-Zip fits a nice niche in between the built-in Windows capabilities and the features of the paid products, and it is able to handle a large variety of file formats in the process.

name: AD
description: Active Directory Domain Services is Microsoftâ€™s Directory Server. It provides authentication and authorization mechanisms as well as a framework within which other related services can be deployed (AD Certificate Services, AD Federated Services, etc). It is an LDAP compliant database that contains objects.

name: ActivePivot
description: The ActivePivot aggregates massive amounts of fast moving data from multiple sources, storing it in its in-memory database to enable optimal decisions in a timely fashion. Combining incremental transactional and analytical processing, the ActivePivot computes sophisticated metrics on data that is updated on the fly without the need for any pre-aggregation. It lets you explore metrics across hundreds of dimensions, analyze live data at its most granular level and perform what-if simulations at unparalleled speed.
usecases: In memory computing and analytics of large datasets.

name: Ansible AWX
description: Ansible AWX is a way to automate apps and IT infrastructure. Application Deployment plus Configuration Management and Continuous Delivery.

name: Ansible Tower
description: Ansible Tower is a way to automate apps and IT infrastructure. Application Deployment plus Configuration Management and Continuous Delivery.

name: Apache Ant
description: Apache Ant is a Java-based build tool. In theory, it is kind of like Make, but without Make's wrinkles.

name: Apache ActiveMQ
description: Apache ActiveMQ is an open source message broker written in Java together with a full Java Message Service client. It provides Enterprise Features which in this case means fostering the communication from more than one client or server.

name: Apache Cassandra
description: Apache Cassandra is a free and open-source distributed wide column store NoSQL database management system designed to handle large amounts of data across many commodity servers, providing high availability with no single point of failure.
comments: Get approval from EA for experimental usage.

name: Apache CouchDB
description: Apache CouchDB is open source database software that focuses on ease of use and having a scalable architecture.

name: Apache HBase Master
description: HBase is an open-source, non-relational, distributed database modeled after Google's Bigtable and written in Java.
usecases: Big data platform - use if you need to process large data sets.

name: Apache HBase Region Server
description: HBase is an open-source, non-relational, distributed database modeled after Google's Bigtable and written in Java.

name: Apache HTTPD-based Webserver
description: The Apache HTTP Server, colloquially called Apache, is a free and open-source cross-platform web server.

name: Apache Hive
description: Apache Hive is a data warehouse software project built on top of Apache Hadoop for providing data query and analysis. Hive gives an SQL-like interface to query data stored in various databases and file systems that integrate with Hadoop.

name: Apache Kafka
comments: Should be used for data transfer and message passing between applications.

name: Apache Thrift
description: The Apache Thrift software framework, for scalable cross-language services development, combines a software stack with a code generation engine to build services that work efficiently and seamlessly between C++, Java, Python, PHP, Ruby, Erlang, Perl, Haskell, C#, Cocoa, JavaScript, Node.js, Smalltalk, OCaml and Delphi and other languages.
comments: May be used in the following recommended use cases: Exposing and consuming service endpoints in RPC style (as an alternative to REST), This is an interim solution, while Communication Layer has not delivered the request-response integration patterns, see Recommended Integration Patterns. Thrift must not be used as a Canonical Message Format. Usage in new projects requires permission from Enterprise Architecture.

name: Apache Tomcat
comments: Should be used as a container for all webenabled Java applications.

name: Apache Xalan for C++ XSLT Processor
Apache Xalan for Java XSLT Processor
Apache Xerces for C++ XML Parser
Apache Xerces for Java XML Parser
Apache Xerces for Perl XML Parser
AppDynamics
usecases: Should be used for metrics gathering on application level.

name: Atlassain Bamboo
comments: Should be used for aytomated building. Provided by SRE

name: Atlassian Bitbucket
comments: Should be used for sorce code management. Provided by SRE

name: Atlassian Confluence
comments: Should be used for team collaboration. Provided by SRE

name: Atlassian Jira
comments: Should be used for issue tracking. Provided by SRE

name: Atlassian Sourcetree
description: Sourcetree simplifies how you interact with your Git repositories so you can focus on coding. Visualize and manage your repositories through Sourcetree's simple Git GUI.

name: Atom
description: Atom is a free and open-source text and source code editor for macOS, Linux, and Microsoft Windows with support for plug-ins written in Node.js, and embedded Git Control, developed by GitHub. Atom is a desktop application built using web technologies.

name: C#
description: C# is a multi-paradigm programming language encompassing strong typing, imperative, declarative, functional, generic, object-oriented (class-based), and component-oriented programming disciplines.
comments: Should not be used unless a vendor application requires C# for integration.

name: Git
description: Git is a free and open source distributed version control system.
comments: Should be used for all new projects.

name: Hadoop distributed file system (HDFS)
description: The HDFS is a distributed, scalable, and portable file system written in Java for the Hadoop framework.
comments: May be used if no interoperability issues exist between producer and consumers.

name: Hamcrest
comments: May be used for all Java developement.

name: Hashicorp Vagrant
usecases: May only be used for testing and local development.

name: Haskell
description: Haskell is a standardized, general-purpose purely functional programming language, with non-strict semantics and strong static typing
comments: Should not be used unless a vendor application requires it for integration.

name: IBM Db2
description: IBM Db2 contains database-server products developed by IBM. These products all support the relational model, but in recent years, some products have been extended to support object-relational features and non-relational structures like JSON and XML.
comments: Should not be used unless where needed by legacy applications. Development of new functionality on these platforms is strongly discouraged.

name: Java
description: Java is a general-purpose computer programming language that is concurrent, class-based, object-oriented, and specifically designed to have as few implementation dependencies as possible.
usecases: No suppport. No infrastructure exists until requested by business
Should be used for all new development projects except mainframe.

name: Javascript
description: JavaScript often abbreviated as JS, is a high-level, dynamic, weakly typed, prototype-based, multi-paradigm, and interpreted programming language.
comments: Should be used for frontend development in web projects.

name: Jfrog Artifactory
comments: Should be used for artifact and library management.

name: Mercurial
description: Mercurial is a distributed revision-control tool for software developers.

name: Nodejs
description: Node.js is an open-source, cross-platform JavaScript run-time environment for executing JavaScript code server-side.
comments: May be used in frontend web development

name: Xray for Jira
description: Manual and Automated Test Management tool for JIRA
comments: May be used for test management. Provided by SRE
